HEADWORD: Weathering
<hw>Weath"er*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The action
of the elements on a rock in altering its color, texture, or
composition, or in rounding off its edges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

